{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}} The '''Disabled Persons' Parking Places (Scotland) Act 2009''' was an [[Act of the Scottish Parliament]] to make provision for the duties of [[Scottish local authorities|local authorities]] in relation to parking places for use by [[Disabled vehicle|disabled persons' vehicles]], which was passed by [[Scottish Parliament|Parliament]] on 26 February 2009 and received Royal Assent on 1 April 2009.<ref>[http://www.opsi.gov.uk/legislation/scotland/acts2009/asp_20090003_en_1 Disabled Persons' Parking Places (Scotland) Act 2009] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090911094417/http://www.opsi.gov.uk/legislation/scotland/acts2009/asp_20090003_en_1 |date=11 September 2009 }} www.opsi.gov.uk, accessed 7 August 2009</ref>
